                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d742">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 341.622a/294</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-23T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 23, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4476. Your 5730, February 21, 7 p.m.<note n="2" xml:id="d742fn2">Not
                        printed.</note> I do not wish to enter into further prolonged discussion of
                        <hi rend="italic">Ausable</hi> case, etc. Before the <pb facs="0699" n="527"
                        xml:id="pg_527"/> British reply is received, I am anxious to obtain, as
                    indicated in my mail despatch No. 4520, December 1, an intimation as to the
                    attitude of the British Government in the matter. If there is no hope that the
                    British Government will discontinue their practice on the representations made,
                    I desire to make the arbitration proposal in my despatch No. 4520, before Mr.
                        <persName corresp="#p_BAJ1">Balfour</persName> replies. Before making this
                    proposal, however, telegraph me your views.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
